      • identityOf

        public static java.lang.String identityOf​(java.lang.Object object)
        Helps track object identities by maintaining a reference identity map.

        IMPORTANT NOTE: Since this method holds references to the objects it identifiers, it prevents garbage collection of those objects, which can cause big memory leaks, but only when Debug is enabled for this class with -DKIVAKIT_DEBUG=Objects or another similar pattern. Be sure you don't have Debug enabled for this class when looking at memory leaks.

        Returns:
        A string representing the identity of the object. The ≡ symbol in math means "identity". Each class has a separate sequence of objects that have been allocated, starting at identity 1. For example, StringList ≡1, ObjectList ≡1, StringList ≡2, etc... This makes is easier to track objects when debug tracing.
